<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-B92E2D9B-AB2E-44A8-8D4F-E6558AF6C3FA" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-B92E2D9B-AB2E-44A8-8D4F-E6558AF6C3FA" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> little white spots</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-50B00AD6-0A38-41AB-B3CF-DCE2951AFA8A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><table id="GUID-53E5F599-B620-44AD-919D-C7253ABD770C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-85B9A974-4A0D-44A5-97D7-DB834219E28D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0E81CB99-0F1F-43EB-97C4-AFF7CC897D7F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0E81CB99-0F1F-43EB-97C4-AFF7CC897D7F-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-3CC7AEEE-B0F6-46BB-ADC5-7756D9211189" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-10FFBF5E-4161-4525-B9B6-81EEB19F41D9-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-10FFBF5E-4161-4525-B9B6-81EEB19F41D9-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-8FCA8508-89A6-4F5D-9AD6-C68714E14671" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-BEC77FCE-E5DD-4423-80FC-24FC9F1F1E55-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BEC77FCE-E5DD-4423-80FC-24FC9F1F1E55-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-096149F5-0F72-4C95-844B-C2953F783FAD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A120E151-FED7-443E-BDA3-B785569CB2BB-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A120E151-FED7-443E-BDA3-B785569CB2BB-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-47775D8E-581A-4D70-A9E7-732A84F30329" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B6DA4607-E70F-430C-B8B8-DF11EFE21EC6-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B6DA4607-E70F-430C-B8B8-DF11EFE21EC6-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-98BAA0D6-AAE4-4A47-9944-BB2DE1259FBF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-424421CB-665D-4796-B991-3F4106628BD1-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-424421CB-665D-4796-B991-3F4106628BD1-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Lot of small white spots in the whole print ( ø &lt; 1 mm) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The top layer of media is visible 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Mostly visible in Gloss-modes 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Mostly visible in high-coverage areas 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Spots are located in random locations 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-532B9FC5-3125-45B2-9FB1-202BF39859A5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p ">No logging available which can pinpoint to this case. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-28726BA5-7125-449B-83E6-F15E5AEB07ED" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM triggers are available 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-8A436BC0-DF05-4105-BE45-4CC1DB874943" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7623626A-F5EC-4A5E-923D-6BDF3FBCEEC7-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7623626A-F5EC-4A5E-923D-6BDF3FBCEEC7-svg.svg"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-BB9BDDD1-E29C-42C5-BF10-2854E3AE4223" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Steps explanation</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-FF911B14-FCE1-46CD-B1CE-F9238B6C82EB" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To do 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Perform manual maintenance, mainly focused on cleaning parts under the top cover (including the top cover itself) and inside the drawer. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the white spots are visible in one or more primary (or mixed) colors or in all colors. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Print a large area of one primary color (set color management OFF in the RIP) 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the ink has been expired 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Clean the ink system 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="02ADJU004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-0A9015C3-DC1C-417D-8B80-D6AE9F8C4B83.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 The (expired) ink replacement procedure including flushing tubes?>02 The ink replacement procedure</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Escalate to Venlo 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The cause is hard to determine. Support from Venlo is required. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace pump tube 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="02DISA026" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-17BE5A1E-1F83-432B-A7C3-6E2D5D312EEC.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 How to remove the pump tube of the ink pump?>02 How to remove the pump tube of the ink pump</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace printhead 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="04DISA002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-75F1003D-F727-49BD-88A7-1CEF7223F097.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document?>04 How to replace a (failing) printhead: Overview document</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the spots are also visible in gloss mode on other kinds of media (Film, paper, etc.). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the number of white spots is significantly larger in the first 50cm after the leading edge. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The number of spots after 50cm can still be present but in lower numbers. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Replace the knife 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><xref keyref="16user002" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-C1454619-27B2-488F-A6FB-B9B0BCC75BA8.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 16 Replace the knife?>16 Replace the knife</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Is there a cutter in the same room (e.g., Zund) that regularly cuts vinyl media? 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place the printer in a room different from the cutter. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Find other sources of pollution outside the printer 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the used media is a Cast-Vinyl 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">15 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the media is past the expiry date 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">In some cases, this issue can be seen in media, which is approx. 1 year old. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">16 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Use another role or batch 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">17 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Use print mode “Gloss Speciality” 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If gloss mode is needed, use this mode; otherwise, use a Matt mode. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">18 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Adjust the temperature of the platen in decrease sensitivity for white spots. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">19 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check if the media is Machine Coated (MC) or Clay coated. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">20 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">This media is not suitable for gloss-mode. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Use a Matt-printmode. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Make sure the printer and its surroundings are clean and free of airborne pollution 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> In the case of Cast-Vinyl, use the Gloss-specialty mode and make sure the media is not expired. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Machine or Clay-coated material is not suitable for gloss-modes. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">Ink needs to be spread evenly over the top layer of the media to give a smooth appearance. Two known causes disrupt the spreading of the ink. As it’s hard to see which mechanism is causing the white spots with the naked eye, a complex flowchart is needed to solve these spots generically. When a microscope (e.g., Dinolite) is used, the different types of white spots can be determined. 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Surfactants (silicone-like chemicals). These chemicals locally change the surface tension of the ink or media surface. In those cases, the ink can coalesce, and the surface of the media will be shown. 
</p><fig id="GUID-B9F4055B-0A36-484B-BD17-6966FC20C491" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-9FCABF9B-CFE1-47D4-9E68-7B5B605F8135-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9FCABF9B-CFE1-47D4-9E68-7B5B605F8135-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">In these cases, the white spots are perfectly round and have a dark halo around it (crater-like shape). In most cases these kinds of white spots are caused by expired vinyl media or polluted ink. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Pollution (physical particles). Pollution will be partly covered by ink. When mechanical forces are applied to the finished print (winding, rubbing, etc.), these particles may vanish, leaving a broken ink layer. 
</p><fig id="GUID-C519D0E3-9C92-4C34-9D28-ACE83B75F859" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7C674E00-13B0-4820-B189-A4A623D5CF99-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7C674E00-13B0-4820-B189-A4A623D5CF99-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">In these cases, a sharp difference between the ink layer and the media color is visible. The shape depends on the shape of the pollution (for example, above a hair/fiber). These kinds of white spots are mostly caused by polluted media or external pollution. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Of course, both causes can be present in the same print. There are also cases where silicone-polluted fibers (cause 1 and 2 together) cause the white spots. 
</p><fig id="GUID-1DF1758A-BA76-480E-96BC-FA950B5622A0" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-BC06D88D-FE48-48D6-89F5-0D4C634DF8CF-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BC06D88D-FE48-48D6-89F5-0D4C634DF8CF-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">In these cases, the appearance is a combination of both causes: white spots with a dark halo, but inside the white spot, the pollution is visible. This combination of causes can be seen when fibers of cut vinyl media have fallen on the media. 
</p></li></ol></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-945E6C60-1212-47DF-9487-92374227D4B4.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>